+id: "EPIC-agentic-methodology-component-arch-001"
+domain: "agentic-methodology"
+capability: "AM-F001"
+
+provenance:
+  source: brief_explicit
+  source_quote: "agentic-methodology / component-architecture (LIVE) — Stage-3 user input"
+  confidence: high
+
+problem_statement: >
+  Every major AI coding tool (GitHub Copilot, Cursor, Windsurf) operates within a single
+  session context — when the session ends, all methodology decisions, play traces, and
+  engineering constraints are discarded (market brief gap 1, validated via MemNexus Feb 2026).
+  Without a compiled three-layer hierarchy (Play → Agent → Skill) with traceable evidence
+  artifacts, engineering actions become ad-hoc: plays inline domain logic, skills are called
+  directly from plays, and evidence files never reach git. For a solo developer, this
+  compounds silently — there is no second reviewer to catch drift before a rebuild resets
+  manually edited compiled artifacts.
+
+intent: >
+  Enable a solo founder to invoke ≥ 95% of engineering actions via plays with full KB
+  traceability, reducing ad-hoc tool drift to < 5% of engineering actions over a 30-day window.
+
+intent_lock:
+  locked_at: "2026-04-18T05:00:00Z"
+  intent_hash: "sha256:dd3d7f4ab3f455115ba3ae31a96f8fe12183f5b0bb68ef9613b5ad13a22e863e"
+  locked_by: "specify-product-stage-5-validate"
+  immutability_note: >
+    Intent is immutable after lock. Features may be added to the ledger as the
+    product evolves, but each must serve this intent. Any change to the intent
+    string requires a successor epic with a new ID (see Product-Drift trigger).
+
+appetite: "2 weeks"
+
+in_scope:
+  - "All 9 component-architecture features (AM-F001 through AM-F009) at Advanced depth — hardening to close evidence and enforcement gaps"
+  - "Play compilation: every play is a compiled artifact traceable to intent.yaml — /create-play --rebuild detects drift and warns"
+  - "Agent delegation enforcement: 100% of domain tasks in plays delegated to agents; /create-play compiler warns on inlined domain logic"
+  - "STM folder whitelist enforcement: zero whitelist violations in rolling 30 days; preflight validators in plays"
+  - "Tether/Vanish protocol coverage: 100% of destructive steps use Tether/Vanish, not raw y/n prompts"
+  - "Evidence and checkpoint substrate: 100% of play steps produce evidence; evidence self-committed per ADR 012; checkpoint rollback success ≥ 95%"
+  - "AI-authorship commit trailer on all play-produced commits (ratchet requirement from audit-attribution capability)"
+
+anti_goals:
+  - "Enterprise governance agents, approval quorum, or signed attestation — requires security_level=high or critical; profile declares elevated"
+  - "Tab-complete or arg-hint CLI improvements to slash commands — those belong to the cli-slash-commands epic"
+  - "Multi-tenant or governance-gated play invocation — post-v1 enterprise milestone (Jul 2026)"
+  - "Brownfield project migration flows — greenfield-first architecture; brownfield is the May 2026 milestone scope"
