+problem_statement: >
+  When an AI-assisted development session ends, all spec decisions — which capabilities
+  to build, which constraints to enforce, which scenarios to validate — are discarded.
+  Without a persistent maturity-ladder engine, teams re-litigate the same architectural
+  questions in every new session, with no record of the constraints that shaped prior
+  decisions. Market brief gap 4 confirms: no AI coding tool connects spec decisions to
+  test generation in a persistent artifact chain (MemNexus Feb 2026, Cuckoo Network Jun 2025).
+  The concrete failure: when an intent.yaml changes upstream, downstream scenarios are not
+  updated — tests pass against stale specs silently, with no second reviewer on a solo project.
+
+intent: >
+  Ensure 100% of intent epics pass validate-intent-epics schema validation before the
+  spec-lock gate, and check-drift detects ≥ 90% of spec-vs-implementation divergences
+  post-merge within the same session.
