+id: "EPIC-work-intelligence-intent-driven-verification-001"
+domain: "work-intelligence"
+capability: "WI-F010"
+
+provenance:
+  source: brief_explicit
+  source_quote: "work-intelligence / intent-driven-verification (WI-F010/F011/F012/F013 all LIVE) — Stage-3 Q4 user inclusion decision"
+  confidence: high
+
+problem_statement: >
+  Test suites in AI-assisted development are written against the implementation, not the
+  original user intent — a defect can be fixed in a way that satisfies the code while
+  violating the original scenario that justified the feature. Without intent-driven eval
+  generation, evals drift from intent after an intent.yaml change: false positive passes
+  occur silently because evals validate stale scenarios. Market brief gap 4 confirms: no
+  AI coding tool connects intent behind a feature to test generation in a persistent artifact
+  chain (Linear, Jira, GitHub Projects — none ship spec-to-test continuity). On a solo
+  project with no second reviewer, a shallow RCA that fixes the symptom instead of the
+  root cause produces a defect that reopens at the next release — every recurrence costs
+  the solo contributor full investigation time with no team to share the load.
+
+intent: >
+  Ensure every Garura play has intent-traceable step evals and every capability has
+  scenario evals that pass on canonical traces, and fix-it closes ≥ 95% of filed defects
+  without reopening within the same milestone window.
+
