+    rationale: >
+      Performance efficiency covers all time-behavior and throughput constraints across
+      the product. The product-level floor is the strictest (< 1s command invocation
+      latency) per the strictest-wins aggregation logic recorded in D-dqp-001. Per-play
+      wall-clock timing is intentionally baselined-not-guessed: every play ships with
+      null measurements and the first instrumented run populates p50/p95/p99. Acceptable
+      targets follow from the baseline in the next profile revision — this is the only
+      discipline that prevents aspirational numbers from anchoring downstream decisions.
+
+  compatibility:
+    relevance: medium
+    targets:
+      - "sync-claude, sync-codex, and sync-droid must each run idempotently on their respective harness host configurations; second run on unchanged source produces zero file-system changes (source: EPIC-engineering-experience-cli-slash-commands-001 + EPIC-engineering-experience-ide-integrations-001)"
+      - "npm install garura succeeds on all supported Node LTS versions; no partial-install broken state on any supported version (source: EPIC-engineering-experience-first-run-onboarding-001)"
+      - "quality-check runs successfully on ≥ 95% of supported stacks without interfering with existing CI configurations (source: EPIC-engineering-observability-quality-signals-001)"
+      - "Codex CLI adapter delivers deterministic CI-mode behavior compatible with script-driven workflows (source: EPIC-engineering-experience-ide-integrations-001)"
+      - "Factory Droid sync completes reliably with parity tests passing across all core plays (source: EPIC-engineering-experience-ide-integrations-001)"
+    rationale: >
+      Compatibility covers the multi-harness (Claude Code, Factory Droids, Codex CLI) and
+      multi-stack interoperability requirements. Garura must co-exist with existing CI
+      configurations and developer environments without interference. Platform scope is
+      macOS/Linux for v1; Windows is post-v1.
+
+  interaction_capability:
+    relevance: high
+    targets:
+      - "WCAG 2.1 AA — org-wide baseline for all UI-rendered outputs (sourced uniformly across all 9 epics)"
+      - "/help lists all available Garura slash commands with one-line descriptions within 1s (source: EPIC-engineering-experience-cli-slash-commands-001)"
+      - "Wizard asks as many questions as required for correctness — no arbitrary cap. Each question must carry context, grounding source, and a recommended default; abandonment risk is managed by question quality, not question count (source: EPIC-engineering-experience-first-run-onboarding-001; user override 2026-04-19)"
+      - "Security posture dashboard shows only actionable items by default — severity filtering prevents cognitive overload (source: EPIC-engineering-observability-quality-signals-001)"
+      - "Every destructive step uses Tether/Vanish gate, not raw y/n prompts — 100% coverage (source: EPIC-agentic-methodology-component-arch-001)"
+    rationale: >
+      WCAG 2.1 AA is the strictest accessibility level cited across all 9 epics (uniform
+      across the set — no epic cited a higher or lower level). Interaction capability also
+      covers discoverability and learnability constraints: the 3-question wizard maximum
+      is a KB-validated tradeoff critical to solo-founder adoption. The Tether/Vanish
+      protocol protects user error on destructive actions.
+
+  reliability:
+    relevance: high
+    targets:
+      - "Play invocation success rate ≥ 90% over rolling 30 days — failed runs produce explicit failure evidence (source: EPIC-agentic-methodology-component-arch-001)"
+      - "Checkpoint rollback success ≥ 95% of failure cases (source: EPIC-agentic-methodology-component-arch-001)"
+      - "Evidence self-committed per ADR 012 — session-end evidence loss rate = 0 (source: EPIC-agentic-methodology-component-arch-001)"
+      - "STM folder whitelist violations = 0 in rolling 30 days (source: EPIC-agentic-methodology-component-arch-001)"
+      - "validate-intent-epics exits 0 on every locked epic in a 30-day window — spec-lock gate is a hard block (source: EPIC-agentic-methodology-l2-spec-driven-001)"
+      - "Atomic install guarantee — npm install garura either succeeds completely or leaves zero modified files (source: EPIC-engineering-experience-first-run-onboarding-001)"
+      - "Defect reopen rate < 5% measured across all fix-it-closed defects in a 30-day window (source: EPIC-work-intelligence-intent-driven-verification-001)"
+    rationale: >
+      Reliability targets are sourced from business_rules containing lockout/retry/rollback/
+      failover language, and from success_scenarios with explicit evidence-based pass rates.
+      The brownfield context (57% features LIVE) means reliability gates primarily protect
+      LIVE features; PARTIAL/PLANNED features carry delivery risk tracked in the risk register.
+
+  security:
+    relevance: high
+    targets:
+      - "OWASP ASVS Level 1 minimum across all product surfaces — floor set by profile.security_level=elevated across all 9 epics"
+      - "No wrong code committed — every commit produced by a play must pass the quality-check gate (lint, type-check, unit tests, security scan) AND match the active quality-profile.yaml targets before merge-pr or ship can proceed; commits that bypass the gate are a blocking defect (source: EPIC-engineering-observability-quality-signals-001 + EPIC-work-intelligence-intent-driven-verification-001)"
+      - "Quality-profile match check — merge-pr verifies the diff does not regress any ISO 25010 target in the active quality-profile.yaml; regression is a blocking failure requiring a decision-manifest entry to proceed (source: EPIC-engineering-observability-quality-signals-001)"
+      - "TLS 1.3 for all remote endpoints — npm registry, remote audit bundle delivery, sync endpoints (sourced across 5 epics: component-arch, l2-spec-driven, l3-intent-driven, ai-governance-audit-attribution, ide-integrations)"
+      - "100% of play-produced commits carry AI-authorship commit trailer — RATCHETED mandatory compliance requirement (source: EPIC-ai-governance-audit-attribution-001; ratchet: ai-usage-traceability)"
+      - "Evidence files attribute every play step to agent or user — step-level attribution is non-negotiable (source: EPIC-ai-governance-audit-attribution-001)"
+      - "Every inferred decision has tier-rationale in decision-manifest.yaml before primary artifact write — zero silent resolutions (source: EPIC-ai-governance-audit-attribution-001 + EPIC-agentic-methodology-l3-intent-driven-001)"
+      - "Compliance audit bundle generated on demand — mandatory when compliance.required=true (source: EPIC-ai-governance-audit-attribution-001)"
+      - "Factory Droid credentials stored in environment variables, not in play files (source: EPIC-engineering-experience-ide-integrations-001)"
+      - "npm package integrity verified via npm audit on every CI build (source: EPIC-engineering-experience-first-run-onboarding-001)"
+      - "STM artifact access governed by folder whitelist per ADR 017 (source: EPIC-agentic-methodology-component-arch-001)"
+      - "Security scan policy baseline — critical/high findings block PRs; medium/low inform only (source: EPIC-engineering-observability-quality-signals-001)"
+    rationale: >
+      Security characteristic is ratcheted by the compliance-mandate package in
+      EPIC-ai-governance-audit-attribution-001 (AG-F004 RATCHET NOTE). The floor is
+      OWASP ASVS Level 1 elevated by three compliance mandates: ai-usage-traceability,
+      audit-trail, and memory-governance. Full derivation in D-dqp-002.
+
+  maintainability:
+    relevance: high
+    targets:
+      - "Every play is a compiled artifact traceable to intent.yaml — direct SKILL.md edits are forbidden (source: EPIC-agentic-methodology-component-arch-001)"
+      - "100% of domain tasks in plays delegated to agents — inlining domain logic in plays is forbidden (source: EPIC-agentic-methodology-component-arch-001)"
+      - "check-drift detects ≥ 90% of spec-vs-implementation divergences post-merge (source: EPIC-agentic-methodology-l2-spec-driven-001)"
+      - "Per-capability level drift below 10% of all active capabilities (source: EPIC-agentic-methodology-l2-spec-driven-001)"
+      - "Lint violations not suppressible without documented justification comment; global rule disables require decision-manifest entry (source: EPIC-engineering-observability-quality-signals-001)"
+      - "All STM→LTM promotions follow documented canonicalization workflow; no silent promotions (source: EPIC-agentic-methodology-l2-spec-driven-001)"
+      - "evals-creator regenerated on every /create-play --rebuild — rebuilt play with unapplied eval updates is a blocking CI failure (source: EPIC-work-intelligence-intent-driven-verification-001)"
+    rationale: >
+      Maintainability is a core differentiator for Garura. The three-layer hierarchy (Play→Agent
+      →Skill) with compiled artifacts, drift detection, and lint discipline are all maintainability
+      mechanisms. The product is self-referential — Garura's own maintainability is governed by
+      the same constraints it enforces on products it manages.
+
+  flexibility:
+    relevance: medium
+    targets:
+      - "Progressive feature-gating required — solo UX cannot assume enterprise governance load; feature set expands per adopter segment (source: project-profile.yaml, expressed in in_scope/anti_goals across epics)"
+      - "sync-claude / sync-codex / sync-droid idempotent — safe to run at any frequency; zero file-system changes on second run without source modification (source: EPIC-engineering-experience-cli-slash-commands-001 + EPIC-engineering-experience-ide-integrations-001)"
+      - "Garura adopter progression: solo-founder → small-squads → enterprise — architecture must scale horizontally without breaking existing plays (source: EPIC-agentic-methodology-component-arch-001 anti_goals)"
+      - "npm package modular design — optional modules excluded from core bundle; package size monitored in CI (source: EPIC-engineering-experience-first-run-onboarding-001)"
+    rationale: >
+      Flexibility covers adaptability (adopter-segment progression) and scalability (from
+      solo to enterprise without architectural rewrites). The progressive-deployment model
+      is a first-class constraint. v1 targets solo and small-squads; enterprise is July 2026.
+      Post-v1 flexibility items (Windows support, multi-tenant governance, IDE adapters beyond
+      Claude Code) are explicitly deferred in anti_goals across epics.
+
+  safety:
+    relevance: low
+    targets:
+      - "Tether/Vanish protocol mandatory at 100% of destructive steps — AskUserQuestion is forbidden; explicit user gate required before any irreversible action (source: EPIC-agentic-methodology-component-arch-001)"
+      - "Atomic install guarantee — failed installs leave zero modified files; partial-install state is a blocking defect (source: EPIC-engineering-experience-first-run-onboarding-001)"
+      - "Conflict detection before sync — any local modification triggers Tether/Vanish gate before overwrite (source: EPIC-engineering-experience-cli-slash-commands-001 + EPIC-engineering-experience-first-run-onboarding-001)"
+    rationale: >
+      Safety in ISO 25010 covers fail-safe behavior and hazard mitigation. Garura is developer
+      tooling — not safety-critical embedded software. Safety relevance is LOW because there is
+      no risk to human life or physical systems. However, the Tether/Vanish protocol, atomic
+      install, and conflict detection cover the operational safety surface: preventing irreversible
+      data loss or broken installation states. No occupational or operational hazard warnings
+      apply.
+
+# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+# SECURITY PROFILE
+# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+
+security_profile:
+  selection: ELEVATED_INTERNAL_TOOLING
+  selection_rationale: >
+    Elevated from STANDARD because profile.compliance.categories carries three mandates
+    (ai-usage-traceability, audit-trail, memory-governance) that fire compliance obligations
+    exceeding baseline posture. Not HIGH_REGULATED because external_regulations_in_scope_v1=[]
+    — SOC2/GDPR/HIPAA are deferred to post-v1 enterprise milestone. Full derivation in D-dqp-004.
+
+  authentication:
+    method: cli-session
+    strength: not_applicable
+    rationale: >
+      No external auth surface in v1. Claude Code harness manages session context.
+      SSO/MFA is Enterprise depth, deferred to July 2026 enterprise milestone.
+
+  authorization:
+    model: flat
+    rationale: >
+      Solo-dev profile (team_size=solo-dev). Single contributor in v1. Progressive RBAC
+      is the post-v1 target for small-squads and enterprise adopter segments.
+
+  data_at_rest:
+    encryption: not_explicitly_mandated_v1
+    rationale: >
+      STM artifacts stored as git objects. Tamper-evident storage is Advanced depth for
+      AG-F004/F005 — explicitly deferred to post-v1 per audit-attribution epic anti_goals.
+      v1 documents this gap in audit bundle's limitations section.
+
+  data_in_transit:
+    encryption: TLS 1.3
+    coverage: >
+      Mandatory for all remote endpoints: npm registry connections, any remote audit bundle
+      delivery, remote sync endpoints (Factory Droids, Codex CLI). Sourced from security
+      constraints across 5 epics (component-arch, l2-spec-driven, l3-intent-driven,
+      ai-governance-audit-attribution, ide-integrations).
+
+  secrets_management:
+    approach: environment-variables-only
+    rationale: >
+      Factory Droid credentials stored in environment variables, not in play files
+      (EE-F004 business rule, source: EPIC-engineering-experience-ide-integrations-001).
+      No secrets management service (Vault, AWS Secrets Manager) in v1 scope.
+
+  audit_trail:
+    coverage: full
+    mechanisms:
+      - "100% of play-produced commits carry AI-authorship commit trailer (RATCHETED — AG-F004)"
+      - "Every play step attributed to agent or user in evidence files (AG-F004)"
+      - "Every inferred decision recorded in decision-manifest.yaml before primary artifact write (AG-F005)"
+      - "Compliance audit bundle generated on demand — includes intent, scope, epics, evidence, decisions (AG-F006)"
+    v1_gaps:
+      - "Tamper-evident storage not implemented in v1 — auditor must trust evidence files are unmodified"
+      - "Line-level AI attribution deferred to post-v1 Advanced depth"
+      - "Historical replay with divergence analysis deferred to Enterprise depth"
+
+  compliance_mandates:
+    - category: ai-usage-traceability
+      status: RATCHETED
+      enforcement: "100% of play-produced commits carry AI-authorship commit trailer regardless of depth selection"
+      source_epic: EPIC-ai-governance-audit-attribution-001
+    - category: audit-trail
+      status: active
+      enforcement: "Every inferred decision in decision-manifest.yaml; step-level attribution in evidence files"
+      source_epics:
+        - EPIC-ai-governance-audit-attribution-001
+        - EPIC-agentic-methodology-l3-intent-driven-001
+        - EPIC-work-intelligence-intent-driven-verification-001
+    - category: memory-governance
+      status: active
+      enforcement: "All STM→LTM promotions follow documented canonicalization workflow; no silent promotions"
+      source_epic: EPIC-agentic-methodology-l2-spec-driven-001
+    - category: token-consumption-tracking
+      status: v1_gap
+      enforcement: "Profile-declared but not yet surfaced in any epic constraint; delivery tracked as post-v1 item"
+      source_epic: null
+    - category: ci-cd-enforcement
+      status: active
+      enforcement: "quality-check as mandatory CI step; EO-F001/F002/F004 coverage; lint blocks on violation"
+      source_epic: EPIC-engineering-observability-quality-signals-001
+    - category: adoption-reporting
+      status: v1_gap
+      enforcement: "Profile-declared but not yet surfaced in any epic constraint; post-v1 item"
+      source_epic: null
