+# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+# RISK REGISTER
+# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+#
+# Risks classified on two axes:
+#   severity: HIGH (3+ epic citations) / MEDIUM (2 citations) / LOW (1 citation)
+#   brownfield_dimension: regression_risk (affects LIVE features) /
+#                         delivery_risk (affects PARTIAL/PLANNED features)
+# Full severity rubric and citation counts in D-dqp-003.
+
+risk_register:
+  - id: RISK-001
+    description: >
+      Developers editing deployed components (e.g., ~/.claude/ files or compiled SKILL.md)
+      directly instead of going through the source-then-sync pipeline, causing silent drift
+      between source and deployed state and losing methodology knowledge in the next rebuild.
+    brownfield_dimension: regression_risk
+    affected_features:
+      - EE-F001 (LIVE — sync-claude deployed state)
+      - EE-F015 (LIVE — play invocation surface)
+      - AM-F001 through AM-F009 (LIVE — component-architecture substrate)
+      - WI-F010 through WI-F013 (LIVE — eval and fix-it plays)
+    source_epics:
+      - EPIC-agentic-methodology-component-arch-001
+      - EPIC-engineering-experience-cli-slash-commands-001
+      - EPIC-engineering-experience-first-run-onboarding-001
+      - EPIC-engineering-experience-ide-integrations-001
+    citation_count: 4
+    severity: high
+    mitigation: >
+      CLAUDE.md hard rule forbids direct edits to deployed components. /create-play --rebuild
+      detects drift and emits Tether/Vanish gate before overwriting. recipe-changes-via-rebake
+      rule enforced in agent system prompt. CI check verifies /help entry count equals play count
+      on every play addition. sync-claude checksums local components before any write.
+
+  - id: RISK-002
+    description: >
+      /sync-claude, /sync-codex, or /sync-droid (or the upgrade flow) overwrites user-customized
+      components in the target harness (~/.claude/, ~/.codex/, Factory Droid workspace) without
+      warning, causing permanent loss of customization with no recovery path for a solo-dev.
+    brownfield_dimension: regression_risk
+    affected_features:
+      - EE-F001 (LIVE — sync-claude)
+      - EE-F017 (LIVE — /sync-claude idempotency surface)
+    source_epics:
+      - EPIC-engineering-experience-cli-slash-commands-001
+      - EPIC-engineering-experience-first-run-onboarding-001
+      - EPIC-engineering-experience-ide-integrations-001
+    citation_count: 3
+    severity: high
+    mitigation: >
+      Conflict detection before sync: /sync-claude, /sync-codex, and /sync-droid each checksum all
+      local components in their respective harness against source before any write; any local
+      modification triggers a Tether/Vanish gate showing the diff before overwrite proceeds.
+      Upgrade flow never silently overwrites customized files across any harness.
+
+  - id: RISK-003
+    description: >
+      AI-authorship attribution gap — Factory Droid runs produce AI-generated commits with no
+      AI-authorship trailer, violating the ai-usage-traceability compliance ratchet. Solo-dev
+      impact: every unattributed Droid commit is a 100% attribution gap for that commit.
+    brownfield_dimension: delivery_risk
+    affected_features:
+      - AG-F004 (PARTIAL — commit hook not yet universally installed)
+      - EE-F004 (PARTIAL — governance-signal capture incomplete for Factory Droids)
+      - AG-F005 (PARTIAL — DSD retroactive audit across 42 plays pending)
+    source_epics:
+      - EPIC-ai-governance-audit-attribution-001
+      - EPIC-engineering-experience-ide-integrations-001
+      - EPIC-agentic-methodology-component-arch-001
+    citation_count: 3
+    severity: high
+    mitigation: >
+      Commit hook enforcement: ship and commit-code plays verify hook is installed before first
+      commit attempt; missing hook is a blocking failure, not a warning. Hook installation is
+      part of first-run onboarding (EE-F012/EE-F011 bootstrap). Factory Droid invocation-context
+      capture is a blocking requirement for EE-F004 completion before Factory Droid functionality
+      is enabled in production.
+
+  - id: RISK-004
+    description: >
+      Developers bypassing schema validation at write time — editing generated epics or downstream
+      artifacts without re-validating against the upstream schema, causing silent drift between
+      spec and implementation that surfaces only at the next spec-review cycle.
+    brownfield_dimension: delivery_risk
+    affected_features:
+      - AM-F010 (PARTIAL — per-capability level enforcement not yet implemented)
+      - AM-F012 (PARTIAL — check-drift scheduled detection not yet wired)
+    source_epics:
+      - EPIC-agentic-methodology-l2-spec-driven-001
+      - EPIC-agentic-methodology-l3-intent-driven-001
+    citation_count: 2
+    severity: medium
+    mitigation: >
+      Lock-gate enforcement is hard: validate-intent-epics must exit 0 before any downstream
+      Stage 5/6 skill can proceed. check-drift scheduled post-merge run in merge-pr play.
+      Quantification regex and no-TBD rule in validate-intent-epics catch schema violations
+      at authoring time.
+
+  - id: RISK-005
+    description: >
+      Skipping distill after merging a PR — learnings from the closed issue evaporate before
+      reaching LTM, degrading the quality of future KB-driven decisions silently with no
+      team reviewer to notice.
+    brownfield_dimension: regression_risk
+    affected_features:
+      - EE-F018 (LIVE — distill post-merge, but reminder-gate may be skipped)
+      - AM-F005 (PARTIAL — automated STM→LTM promotion not fully wired)
+    source_epics:
+      - EPIC-engineering-experience-cli-slash-commands-001
+      - EPIC-agentic-methodology-l2-spec-driven-001
+    citation_count: 2
+    severity: medium
+    mitigation: >
+      Distill reminder step added to merge-pr play post-merge sequence; the reminder emits a
+      Tether/Vanish gate if distill has not been run within the same session. distill and
+      capture-learning plays enforce canonicalization before promotion.
+
+  - id: RISK-006
+    description: >
+      Silent resolution of inferred decisions without writing decision-manifest.yaml — the
+      Decision Surfacing Discipline (Defect 23) is violated, leaving decisions only in
+      conversation history with no durable artifact for compliance review.
+    brownfield_dimension: delivery_risk
+    affected_features:
+      - AG-F005 (PARTIAL — DSD not retroactively audited across all 42 plays)
+    source_epics:
+      - EPIC-ai-governance-audit-attribution-001
+      - EPIC-agentic-methodology-l3-intent-driven-001
+    citation_count: 2
+    severity: medium
+    mitigation: >
+      DSD rule enforced in agent system prompt: every inferred decision goes to
+      decision-manifest.yaml BEFORE the primary artifact write. The skill write order in
+      generate-intent-epics and all other decision-producing skills writes the manifest first.
+      Coverage sweep across all 42+ decision-producing plays is in-scope for the
+      audit-attribution epic's 2-week appetite.
+
+  - id: RISK-007
+    description: >
+      npm package size growth when optional modules are bundled with the core package,
+      causing install times exceeding 5 minutes and triggering first-impression abandonment
+      before the solo-founder evaluator reaches the wizard.
+    brownfield_dimension: delivery_risk
+    affected_features:
+      - EE-F010 (PLANNED — wizard not yet implemented)
+      - EE-F011 (PARTIAL — public npm package not yet published)
+    source_epics:
+      - EPIC-engineering-experience-first-run-onboarding-001
+    citation_count: 1
+    severity: low
+    mitigation: >
+      Optional modules excluded from the core npm package. Package size monitored in CI with a
+      budget threshold that fails the CI step if exceeded. Only required dependencies in the
+      core bundle.
+
+  - id: RISK-008
+    description: >
+      Coverage-percentage masking shallow assertions — high coverage percentages achieved
+      by covering only happy-path code paths, providing false confidence that defects are
+      caught when scenario coverage is actually shallow.
+    brownfield_dimension: delivery_risk
+    affected_features:
+      - EO-F001 (PARTIAL — coverage delta per PR not yet wired; happy-path bias possible)
+    source_epics:
+      - EPIC-engineering-observability-quality-signals-001
+    citation_count: 1
+    severity: low
+    mitigation: >
+      Coverage delta (not absolute percentage) is the primary surfaced metric per PR. Mutation
+      testing is documented as a post-v1 planned enhancement for coverage masking detection.
+      Developers warned in quality-check output that high coverage does not guarantee scenario
+      coverage.
+
+  - id: RISK-009
+    description: >
+      Fixing symptom before completing 5-whys RCA — quick fixes without root-cause analysis
+      are the primary source of reopened defects; recurrence costs the solo contributor full
+      investigation time with no team to share the load.
+    brownfield_dimension: regression_risk
+    affected_features:
+      - WI-F012 (LIVE — RCA template in place but enforcement relies on agent system prompt)
+      - WI-F013 (LIVE — fix-it loop closure, but shallow RCA can slip through)
+    source_epics:
+      - EPIC-work-intelligence-intent-driven-verification-001
+    citation_count: 1
+    severity: low
+    mitigation: >
+      fix-it enforces 5-whys RCA before proposing any fix. The RCA template is a required
+      output before fix-it enters the implementation step. A shallow RCA (fewer than 3 why
+      levels) is a blocking failure requiring the developer to deepen analysis. Regression
+      test mandatory on every fix before fix-it marks the defect as closed.
+
