+# fix-it Delivery — Issue #261
+
+**Title:** .garura/ vs .meridian/ migration half-done — skills, agents, installer disagree on config path; KB path hardcoded workspace-relative in agents
+
+## Root Cause
+
+Forward migration from `.meridian/` to `.garura/` was partial. Engine/STM/memory targets had moved to `.garura/`, but 68 source files still hardcoded `.meridian/core/config.yaml` reads, the installer wrote `.meridian/`, and two agents hardcoded KB paths to source-only `core/components/memory/` locations. Result: consumer projects could not bootstrap; every play halted at its readiness check.
+
+## Fix Strategy
+
+Complete the forward migration in one coherent PR:
+
+1. Installer writes `.garura/` and downloads from `kapilvirenahuja/garura`.
+2. Sync scripts deploy memory to `~/.garura/core/memory/`.
+3. Rename `.meridian/core/config.yaml` → `.garura/core/config.yaml` (via `git mv`) and update its internal paths + project name.
+4. Agents (product-keeper, market-analyst) read KB via `ltm_context.core_base` — no hardcoded paths.
+5. Bulk rename `.meridian/core/config.yaml` → `.garura/core/config.yaml` across 13 agents, 22 plays, 15+ skills, and memory reference docs.
+
+Blast radius: 68 files, 8 commits grouped by concern.
+
+## Files Modified
+
+- Installer: `installer/install.sh`
+- Sync: `core/components/skills/sync-{claude,droids}/scripts/sync.sh`
+- Config: `.garura/core/config.yaml` (renamed from `.meridian/...`)
+- Agents KB: `core/components/agents/{product-keeper,market-analyst}.md`
+- Agents bulk: 13 agent files (`.meridian/` → `.garura/`)
+- Plays: 22 SKILL.md files
+- Skills: 15+ SKILL.md files
+- Memory: reference docs and fixtures
+
+## Ship Record
+
+| Field | Value |
+|-------|-------|
+| PR | [#263](https://github.com/kapilvirenahuja/garura/pull/263) |
+| PR state | MERGED |
+| Merge SHA | `53c30071a19aea9ab6326b70be8d1077ee11f420` |
+| Base branch | `main` |
+| Feature branch | `fix/261-garura-meridian-migration-drift` (deleted local + remote) |
+| review-pr.bypass | true (gate skipped) |
+| distill | completed, no_learnings=true |
+
+## Resolution Trace Summary
+
+Per `resolution-trace.yaml`: architecture grounding was available via project LTM for config path shape and KB layering; core LTM contributed conventions for sync target paths. No LLM-only fallbacks on load-bearing decisions.
+
+## Step Evals
+
+| Eval | Result |
+|------|--------|
+| SE-1 (F1) Checkpoint approved before implementation | PASS — Tether recorded in status file |
+| SE-2 (F2/C3) RCA identifies specific file+logic+why | PASS — rca.yaml RC1–RC5 |
+| SE-3 (F3/C4) Alternatives considered w/ rejection reason | PASS — design.yaml |
+| SE-4 (F4) Ship evidence shows commit SHA + PR merged + branch deleted | PASS |
+| SE-5 (F5) Issue #261 exists + open at validation | PASS |
+| SE-6 (F6) Implementation files ⊆ design affected_files (or deviation logged) | PASS |
+| SE-7 (F7) code-builder input contained STM paths only, no brief | PASS |
+| SE-8 (C5) Risks have severity levels | PASS |
+| SE-9 (C11/F8) Resolution trace populated | PASS |
+
+## Scenario Evals
+
+- **SCE-1 (Developer):** evidence artifact contains merge SHA, PR URL, branch-deleted confirmation, RCA, design, implementation record — PASS
+- **SCE-2 (Tech Lead):** checkpoint brief contained root cause, blast radius, strategy, alternatives w/ rejection, risk table, confidence — PASS
+- **SCE-3 (QA):** PR body + evidence contain changes list, RCA reference, blast radius, approval-before-implementation timestamps — PASS
+
+## Notes
+
+Blast radius (68 files) was 5× the fix-it threshold (~10). Because the 5 root causes were all facets of one coherent forward migration and splitting would have left the consumer-project bootstrap broken between PRs, the checkpoint explicitly surfaced the scope and the user approved (Tether) the single-PR execution.
+
+The initial design proposed leaving `.meridian/core/config.yaml` in place as "functionally harmless during transition." That assumption proved wrong in practice — once 68 files were updated to read `.garura/core/config.yaml`, subsequent play invocations failed with config-not-found. The fix was added mid-execution via `git mv`. Captured as a risk-assessment calibration signal for future transitions but not a reusable domain learning per distill.
