+rca:
+  issue_number: 261
+  title: ".garura/ vs .meridian/ migration half-done — skills, agents, installer disagree on config path; KB path hardcoded workspace-relative in agents"
+
+  summary: >
+    Four load-bearing defects block Garura's bootstrapping in consumer projects.
+    The codebase started migrating from .meridian/ to .garura/ (engine reads
+    .garura/core/config.yaml; STM root is .garura/project/issues/; deployed memory
+    is ~/.garura/core/memory/), but source components (66 files), the installer
+    script, sync-claude, and two agents' hardcoded KB paths were never updated.
+    When a consumer project runs the installer (which writes .meridian/core/config.yaml),
+    all plays halt reading config. When agents try to resolve KB domain knowledge,
+    they reference core/components/memory/knowledge/ — a source-repo path never
+    available in deployed environments.
+
+  root_causes:
+    - id: RC1
+      symptom: "Installer writes .meridian/core/config.yaml; all plays expect .garura/core/config.yaml"
+      cause: >
+        The installer script (installer/install.sh) was never updated during the
+        engine+STM migration. It still references .meridian/core/config.yaml (lines
+        56, 98, 209, 217, 280, 287) and downloads from the kapilvirenahuja/meridian
+        repository (line 9, REPO="kapilvirenahuja/meridian"). When a consumer runs
+        the installer, it creates .meridian/ structure. But 66 files in core/components
+        (agents, plays, skills) all contain hardcoded grep/yq commands reading from
+        .meridian/core/config.yaml — they work for the garura repo itself (which
+        still has .meridian/core/config.yaml), but fail in a consumer project that
+        only has .garura/.
+
+      files_affected:
+        - installer/install.sh
+
+      why_wrong: >
+        The engine (core/engine/src/lib/constants.ts line 28) reads
+        ".garura/core/config.yaml at runtime" per its docblock. The STM root
+        (.garura/project/issues/) is hard-coded in the engine. The deployed
+        global memory is ~/.garura/core/memory/ (confirmed by sync-claude and
+        sync-droids). The repository is named garura; the project name is Garura
+        in CLAUDE.md. The migration direction is complete except source components
+        were never updated. Installer is the entry point for consumer projects — it
+        must write .garura/, not .meridian/.
+
+    - id: RC2
+      symptom: "66 source files read .meridian/core/config.yaml; breaks in consumer projects"
+      cause: >
+        Every agent markdown file (13 files), every play SKILL.md file (22 files),
+        and many skill files (15+) contain hardcoded grep/yq commands like:
+        `grep -A5 '^stm:' .meridian/core/config.yaml | grep 'base-path'`.
+        These are in the "readiness" section of SKILL.md files that execute
+        during play initialization. When a consumer project has only .garura/
+        (from the migrated installer), these grep commands fail with exit code 1,
+        and every play halts at the "Hard halt" constraint.
+
+      files_affected:
+        - "All 13 agents (13 files total)"
+        - "All 22 plays' SKILL.md files"
+        - "Skills: sync-claude/scripts/sync.sh, sync-droids/scripts/sync.sh, and 15+ others"
+
+      examples:
+        - "core/components/plays/fix-it/SKILL.md:51 — `grep '^\s*base-path:' .meridian/core/config.yaml`"
+        - "core/components/plays/review-pr/SKILL.md:62-67 — five separate yq/grep calls on .meridian/core/config.yaml"
+        - "core/components/agents/intent-resolver.md:51 — documents that config_path must point to `.meridian/core/config.yaml`"
+
+      why_wrong: >
+        These are not prose references (which could live as decorative text). These
+        are hardcoded file paths used in shell script execution (bash grep/yq within
+        SKILL.md readiness sections). When the file doesn't exist, the entire play
+        fails before any domain work begins. The path resolution MUST match where
+        the installer creates the file.
+
+    - id: RC3
+      symptom: "Agents hardcode KB path as core/components/memory/knowledge/; fails in consumer projects"
+      cause: >
+        Two agents (product-keeper.md:67, market-analyst.md:61-62) document their
+        KB discovery path as "core/components/memory/knowledge/domain/" and
+        "core/components/memory/knowledge/arch/". This is a relative path from
+        the source repository root. It is never available in a consumer project,
+        where core/components/ doesn't exist. The deployed KB is at
+        ~/.garura/core/memory/knowledge/ (or .garura/core/memory/ in project mode).
+
+      files_affected:
+        - "core/components/agents/product-keeper.md:67"
+        - "core/components/agents/market-analyst.md:61-62"
+
+      why_wrong: >
+        These agents document the KB discovery path in their "Input Context"
+        sections, which are read at invocation time by plays. When the agents
+        are deployed and invoked in a consumer project (which has no core/
+        directory), they cannot resolve the path and will fail when they try
+        to read the KB. The correct path is the deployed path:
+        ~/.garura/core/memory/knowledge/{domain,arch}/ for global mode, or
+        .garura/core/memory/knowledge/{domain,arch}/ for project mode.
+
+    - id: RC4
+      symptom: "sync-claude and sync-droids deploy memory to ~/.meridian/core/memory/, not ~/.garura/core/memory/"
+      cause: >
+        Both sync-claude/scripts/sync.sh (lines 24, 27) and sync-droids/scripts/sync.sh
+        (lines 22, 25) set MEMORY_TARGET to ".meridian/core/memory" (project mode) or
+        "~/.meridian/core/memory" (global mode). These scripts are the deployment
+        mechanism for the memory layer. When run, they copy core/components/memory/ to
+        the wrong location, and subsequent plays that read from ~/.garura/core/memory/
+        (as expected by ltm_context and agent documentation) find nothing.
+
+      files_affected:
+        - "core/components/skills/sync-claude/scripts/sync.sh:24, 27"
+        - "core/components/skills/sync-droids/scripts/sync.sh:22, 25"
+
+      why_wrong: >
+        The memory layer is part of the garura framework, not meridian. The deployed
+        global paths must be ~/.garura/core/memory/, and project-scoped paths must
+        be .garura/core/memory/, to match the directory structure already established
+        by the engine and .garura/ folder whitelist.
+
+    - id: RC5
+      symptom: "Garura repo's own .meridian/core/config.yaml still names itself 'Meridian' and references .meridian/ paths"
+      cause: >
+        The project's own config file (at .meridian/core/config.yaml, checked in) defines:
+        - project.name: Meridian (should be Garura)
+        - github.repo: kapilvirenahuja/meridian.git (should be kapilvirenahuja/garura.git)
+        - ltm.source: ./core/components/memory/ (correct)
+        - ltm.project-target: ./.meridian/core/memory/ (should be ./.garura/core/memory/)
+        - ltm.global-target: ~/.meridian/core/memory/ (should be ~/.garura/core/memory/)
+        - All stm and product sections still reference .meridian/ paths
+
+      files_affected:
+        - ".meridian/core/config.yaml (entire file, ~60 lines)"
+
+      why_wrong: >
